sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (serving cert)
    participant RESTProxy as REST Proxy Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: Model Registry REST API Access (with OAuth Proxy)

    Client->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>OAuthProxy: HTTPS/443 (reencrypt)<br/>OpenShift OAuth token
    OAuthProxy->>OAuthProxy: SAR check:<br/>get services/{name} in namespace
    OAuthProxy->>RESTProxy: HTTP/8080<br/>plaintext (localhost)<br/>Trusted after SAR
    RESTProxy->>DB: TCP 5432/3306<br/>Optional SSL<br/>DB credentials (Secret ref)
    DB-->>RESTProxy: Query results
    RESTProxy-->>OAuthProxy: REST API response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>Client: JSON response

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Operator Reconciliation

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as ModelRegistryReconciler

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>HTTPS/TLS<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CRUD resources<br/>(Deployments, Services, Routes,<br/>NetworkPolicies, RBAC, Groups)<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Read Pod logs (status)<br/>HTTPS/TLS<br/>ServiceAccount token

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 3: CRD Storage Version Migration

    participant MigMgr as StorageMigrationManager

    MigMgr->>K8sAPI: Check CRD storedVersions<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>ServiceAccount token
    MigMgr->>K8sAPI: Create StorageVersionMigration<br/>or manual patch<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>MigMgr: Migration status
